title: ADOPTABLE PET: LIVING FREE
text:
1:20 p.m. ADOPTABLE PET: LIVING FREE Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Princess Leah is available for adoption. COURTESY OF LIVING FREE Related article » Animal’s name: Princess Leah
Breed: Female domestic short hair calico tabby
Date of birth: June 16
About the animal: Princess Leah has become a popular kitten at Living Free. Besides being cute, she has a big personality. She is sweet, smart and playful. Princess Leah has a soft coat of calico/tabby fur.
Agency: Living Free, a donor supported, nonprofit, no kill animal sanctuary
Location: 54250 Keen Camp Road in Mountain Center off Highway 74, 15 minutes from Idyllwild
Information: 951-491-1898 or, to view all of Living Free’s adoptable cats and dogs, go to living-free.org
Contact the writer: community@pe.com
